        <span id="_ctl0_contentBody_lblBody"><p>Ecwid is a hosted software solution for making an online store or allows you to sell a product online using your existing website. The platform is tailored for small to medium and enterprise business that have already a website and simply want to add an online store to it.
Ecwid is the easiest and cost-effective tool available in the eCommerce market that offers complete eCommerce solutions. Ecwid allows you to setup catalogs of products, add photos, pricing, weight for each product. The ability to define shipping rates, accept credit card payment has never been easy as using Ecwid.</p>

<p>Ecwid is the cheapest shopping cart in the market which offers a 4 pricing plan. Their free plan gives you an opportunity to try out their system plus also sell up to 10 products absolutely free, no transaction fees and an unlimited bandwidth. If the business is moving then you can move to their Venture Plan at a cost of $15 you can increase your product limits to 100 products. The 3rd plan is the Business Plan at a cost of $35, you get limits of 2500 product listing to your website and a whole new experience and more features. If you a large enterprise that holds tons of product range, than Ecwid got you covered. With the Unlimited plan, you free to add as many products as you need and all this for just $99 per month. As you can see, Ecwid perfect eCommerce partner, whether you are a small business that wants to try out the eCommerce market or large enterprise, Ecwid got you covered.</p>

<p>One of the advantages you will get from Ecwid is the flawless user interface. Ecwid is plug and play system, all you need to do is enter your email and password then you are ready to go. The admin panel clean and all the store settings and configuration options at right clearly visible.
</p>

<p>Ecwid has a few key features that every eCommerce business will go crazy about such as the responsive storefronts, that allows you website to display flawlessly across all devices - desktop, tablet or mobile. Their point-of-sale (POS) allows you to take payments on an IOS device. Another noticeable feature of Ecwid is language detection. Ecwid supports up to 45 different languages, so customers can view your store in their own language this is done automatically using the customer's browser settings.</p>

<p>The Ecwid features you can expect are; a variety of payment and shipping methods, easy checkout process, real-time shipping rates, store management that is equipped all product management tools, iOS and Android App for your store, level 1 PCI compliant, SEO, sell on multiple sites and smoothly integrates with WordPress, Joomla, Facebook, Tumblr, WIX, etc.
They also offer an App Market, which holds around 48 add-on features that you can add your eCommerce website.</p>

<p>The Ecwid features you can expect are; a variety of payment and shipping methods, easy checkout process, real-time shipping rates, store management that is equipped all product management tools, iOS and Android App for your store, level 1 PCI compliant, SEO, sell on multiple sites and smoothly integrates with WordPress, Joomla, Facebook, Tumblr, WIX, etc.
They also offer an App Market, which holds around 48 add-on features that you can add your eCommerce website.</p>

<blockquote> <p><i> <b>If the above does not convince you to use Ecwid then here is a short summary of  the Pros and Cons of Ecwid:</b></i></p></blockquote>

<p><b>Pros:</b><p>
<ol>
<li>Low price, with free plan available</li>
<li>Easy way to add a store to an existing website</li>
<li>Multi-language support</li>
<li>Responsive designs and point of sale are available</li>
<li>App store to control your website on the go via iOS or Android.</li>
<li>Plugins for major platforms, WordPress, Drupal, Wix, Joomla, Facebook, etc.</li>
</ol>
<p><b>Cons:</b></p>
<ol>
<li>Free plan is not good for SEO perspective</li>
<li>Phone and live chat are only available for expensive plans</li>
<li>Needs manual coding and setup</li>
<li>Limited apps available is the App Market</li>
</ol>

<p>In conclusion, Ecwid is simple, cost-effective way to add an eCommerce store to your website and start selling online. It's a powerful eCommerce tool, easy to setup and with a great user panel. If you are new to the eCommerce business than Ecwid platform is the best way to test the viability of your products into the market with the Free plan. The platform is flexible and scalable to all business types. Don't be in the dark and sign up today for your free Ecwid plugin for your website, this just might be the beginning of a new exciting profit making breakthrough your business was looking .</p></span>
